name: Legend Unwritten
description: As preparations to toast the legendary James T. Kirk get underway, the personal effects gathered to help pay tribute begin to change or disappear! Can you determine what kind of temporal disturbance is causing this before Kirk himself vanishes?
rules:
-- Unique Supply Missions are available during the event. Open the Event to access them.
-- Using any version of Dax, Kirk, Kim, or Technician Fisher will provide a bonus to Supply Missions.
-- Every Supply Mission you complete earns you Event Victory Points. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock Threshold Rewards!
-- Community Rewards are only available during Phase 1. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock these rewards before the phase change!
-- In this event, Squadrons may also compete to advance up the Squadron leaderboards. Join a Squadron to get more rewards!
bonus_text: Crew Bonus: Dax, Kirk, Kim, Fisher
rewards_teaser: Reach Rank 1 by gaining Victory Points from Event Supply Missions!

screens.text: "Captain, thanks for joining us for the tribute to Captain Kirk. I figured since the temporal anomaly crisis has deposited so many legends here, we might as well pay tribute to one of Starfleet's finest in honor of his birthday."

"I've been planning this event for weeks. Things have been going smoothly up until today. Several items from Kirk's past that we gathered to put on display have gone missing. And I haven't seen my guest of honor in at least a half an hour. I better go check on him."

"I don't think this is any normal case of misplaced items. These pictures of Kirk...something's off about them. He's beginning to fade. Some of the images have changed or gone blank. And I'm picking up high chroniton readings. Which must mean--"

"He's fading away! Just like the pictures! Captain, I don't know what's going on, but with the chroniton readings Jadzia picked up, someone must be tinkering with the past. Please help us find out who and put a stop to them."

"Nice work, Captain. You've confirmed my suspicions. There's definitely a temporal disturbance at play and, judging from what you've gathered, the culprit is here somewhere. Wait a second...who's taking the stage? He looks just like Captain Kirk, except for that scar..."

"'Tribute to a Legend?' 'Starfleet's Finest?' You can't mean James T. Kirk? A man with all the spine of a tribble? You idiots are blinded to who he truly is, but I'll rewrite history to celebrate someone more worthy of the honor."

responses.text: "Captain Kirk? Why are you acting this way?"
"How dare you speak that way about Kirk!"

screens.text: "Isn't it obvious? To take my rightful place in history. This fool doesn't deserve all the praise you're heaping on him. And yet you all lift him up and try to do away with me."

"Are you blind? I'm Kirk, just better. Starfleet will tell you I was born from a transporter accident that split me from what they think is the 'real' Kirk, but I've always been there. That transporter just removed all the useless noise."

"He doesn't deserve all of this pomp and circumstance. Have you seen the size of his temporal violations file? It might be the only thing in the galaxy to match his ego. I'm here to set the record straight."

"How did he do that? He's gone, Captain, but it's a sure bet that he's gone to tamper with Captain Kirk's past again  We need you to put a stop to him once and for all. Figure out where he's gone in the timeline, set it straight, and apprehend him."
